46.0
=======

GNOME Tweaks 46.0 is the first stable release of Tweaks to use GTK 4 and libadwaita. The GTK 4 port has been a long-running migration driven by two contributors:
Ezike Ebuka and Maximiliano Sandoval R.

GNOME Tweaks now depends on GTK 4, libadwaita, gsettings-desktop-schemas,
and libgudev.

* Contributions:
  - !53 Search for shell themes in default gnome-shell theme dir (Carlo Lobrano)
  - !94 Support selecting an accel profile for touchpads (Evan Goode)
  - !110 Remove overamplification option (Automeris naranja)
  - !121 Add dark style background option in appearance (Akatsuki Rui)
  - !128 Remove "Disable Touchpad While Typing" (Automeris naranja)
  - !131 Use gnome.post_install in meson (Bobby Rong)
  - !133 Avoid using Gtk.PropertyExpression (Chris Williams)

* Issues closed:
  - #329 "Caps Lock behavior ü°í Disabled" setting is unintuitive (Automeris naranja)
  - #369 Focus Mode "Secondary-Click" is misnamed (Frank Dana)
  - #408 Let tweaks show up when users search "startup applications" (Vancha)
  - #443 Remove "Legacy Window Titles" tweak (Automeris naranja)
  - #450 Ensure gettext and locale are initialized correctly (Evan Welsh)

* Translation updates:
  - Belarusian (Vasil Pupkin)
  - Chinese (China) (Luming Zh)
  - Czech (Daniel Rusek)
  - Danish (Alan Mortensen)
  - Galician (Fran Dieguez)
  - Georgian (Ekaterine Papava)
  - German (Christian Kirbach, J√ºrgen Benvenuti)
  - Hebrew (Yosef Or Boczko)
  - Hungarian (Bal√°zs √ör)
  - Occitan (post 1500) (Quentin PAG√àS)
  - Persian (Danial Behzadi)
  - Polish (Piotr DrƒÖg)
